Joshua Hull (jhull@clemson.edu)
CPSC 4040-001 Fall 2014 Lab 5

USAGE
tonemap -g value input_image [output_image] OR
tonemap -c input_image [output_image]

ABSTRACT
Tonemap a HDR or EXR image with either gamma correction or global convolution of
the luminance of the image.

COMPILING
Simply type 'make' from the root directory.

PARAMATERS
* input_image: HDR or EXR image to tone map. Required.
* value: The value of gamma when doing gamma correction. Required.
* output_image: The name of the image to write to. Any format supported by OIIO.
  See BUGS below. Optional.

INTERACTION
* Press 'q', 'Q', or ESC to exit the program.
* Press 'w' or 'W' to write the tonemapped image to output_image. If no
output_image is given then no image is written.
* Press 's' or 'S' to switch between the original and tone mapped images.

BUGS
Program cannot write to hdr images. Program tries to validate command line
parameters as best it can but it it possible to give it bad values. The USAGE
above will always work.

EXAMPLES
Ocean_simple.png : Gamma of 0.18125.
Ocean_convolution.png : Default values.

smallDesignStudio_simple.png: Gamma of 0.085.
smallDesignStudio_convolution.png : Default values.
